<style>
  .article_column-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 320px;
    border-radius: 11px;
  }
  img.article_column-image {
    overflow: hidden;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 50% 50%;
  }
  .article_column-image-border {
    border: 1px solid rgba(60, 31, 27, 0.30);
  }
  .article_column {
      height: max-content;
  }
  .article_column-third {
    width: calc(33.3333334% - 33.3333334px);
  }
  .article_column-half {
    width: calc(50% - 25px);
  }
  .article_column-text-third-top {
    padding-top: 81px;
  }
  .article_column-text ul {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
    color: #3c1f1b;
    margin-top: -10px;
    padding-left: 34px;
  }
  @media(max-width: 1450px) {
    .article_column-half {
    width: calc(50% - 15px);
  }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
      gap: 30px;
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 114px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 1250px) {
    .article_column-third {
        width: calc(50% - 15px);
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 81px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 950px) {
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 114px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 750px) {
    .article_column-text ul {
      margin-top: -12px;
      padding-left: 32px;
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 0;
    }
    .article_column-half {
      width: 100%
    }
    .article_column-third {
        width: 100%;
        gap: 30px;
    }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
        gap: 30px;
    }
    .rebranding_container {
        gap: 40px;
    }
    .article_column-text .h3-heading-pp, .article_column-text .h3-heading-ss {
        text-align: center;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 450px) {
    .article_column-image {
      height: 250px;
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="rebranding_container block-flex-wrap block-gap-50">
  <div class="rebranding-section-title block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center">
    <h2 class="h2-heading-ss">
      How to Identify a 
      <span class="h2-heading-pp">
        Fake Louis Vuitton Bag
      </span>
      : 6 Essential Signs to Spot a Counterfeit
    </h2>
    <p class="body-text block-max-width">
      <strong>Louis Vuitton</strong> is one of the most counterfeited luxury brands in the world. Its signature monogram, timeless designs, and premium craftsmanship make LV bags a target for knockoffs — from street vendors to online listings.
<br><br>
If you're trying to determine <strong>whether a Louis Vuitton bag is real or fake</strong>, here are six key signs to look for before you buy.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="article_columns-wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-start-center">
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv-blog_seo-1.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Louis Vuitton Bag: Low-Quality Materials and Finishes">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 1</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Low-Quality Materials and Finishes</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
         <strong>Authentic Louis Vuitton</strong> bags are made from <strong>premium materials</strong> like Monogram Canvas, Damier Ebene, Epi Leather, and Vachetta leather. These materials are durable, with a high-end texture and finish.
<br><br>
Red flags for fakes:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Plastic-feeling canvas or overly shiny leather</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Rigid or uneven surfaces</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Strong chemical smell</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
        <span class="italic"><strong>Tip:</strong> Real Louis Vuitton canvas has a soft, supple feel with a light leather scent — never rubbery or stiff.</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv-blog_seo-2.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Louis Vuitton Bag: Misaligned Monogram Pattern">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 2</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Misaligned Monogram Pattern</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Louis Vuitton’s iconic monogram pattern is <strong>perfectly aligned</strong> on authentic bags — even across seams, zippers, and flaps.
<br><br>
What to watch for:
        </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text"><strong>Cut-off or misaligned LV logos</strong></p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Asymmetrical placement</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Upside-down logos on models where they shouldn't be (e.g. Speedy 30)</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
        <span class="italic"><strong>Remember:</strong> Louis Vuitton uses a single canvas piece on some bags, so <strong>upside-down logos</strong> are expected on some models like the Speedy — but not others.</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv-blog_seo-3.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Louis Vuitton Bag: Inaccurate Date Codes or Missing Heat Stamps">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 3</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Inaccurate Date Codes or Missing Heat Stamps</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Genuine LV bags feature:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">A <strong>heat stamp</strong> that reads “LOUIS VUITTON Paris” (with “Made in France”, “Spain”, “USA”, or “Italy”)</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">A <strong>date code</strong> (not a serial number) that reflects the bag’s manufacturing week and year</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Fake LV bags often:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Use the wrong date code format</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Misplace the code or make it unreadable</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Have poorly stamped or misspelled logos (e.g. “LOIUS VUITTON”)</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv-blog_seo-4.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Louis Vuitton Bag: Cheap Hardware and Zippers">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 4</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Cheap Hardware and Zippers</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Authentic Louis Vuitton hardware is made of <strong>high-quality brass or gold-toned metal</strong>, engraved cleanly and polished to a shine.
<br><br>
Counterfeit signs:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Lightweight or plastic hardware</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Tarnished or peeling finish</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Engraving looks etched, too shallow or uneven</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          LV zippers are smooth, sturdy, and often engraved with “Louis Vuitton.” Fakes may have generic or off-brand zipper pulls.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv-blog_seo-5.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Louis Vuitton Bag: Poor Stitching Quality">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 5</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Poor Stitching Quality</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Louis Vuitton bags have <strong>impeccable stitching</strong> — even, tight, and symmetrical. Authentic models often have:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">A specific number of stitches per handle tab</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Color-accurate thread (often mustard-yellow)</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Zero loose threads or uneven lines</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
         Fake bags often have:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Sloppy or crooked stitches</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Loose threads</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Wrong thread color</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv-blog_seo-6.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Louis Vuitton Bag: Wrong Interior Materials and Tag Details">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 6</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Wrong Interior Materials and Tag Details</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          The inside of a real Louis Vuitton bag is <strong>cleanly finished</strong> with <strong>suede-like Alcantara</strong>, canvas, or high-end microfiber.
<br><br>
Warning signs:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Shiny, plastic-feeling lining</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Incorrect font or alignment on the interior tag</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Missing, blurry, or off-center heat stamps</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

